Rivers State Governor and Visitor to the Rivers State University, Nyesom Ezenwo Wike, has sacked the Vice Chancellor of the institution, Professor Blessing Chimezie Didia. Also relieved of his appointment is the Deputy Vice Chancellor (Administration), Professor Magnus Oruwari. A statement issued by the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Education, Dagogo Hart, said the governor approved the appointment of Professor Opuenebo B. Owei, Deputy Vice Chancellor (Academics) as the acting Vice Chancellor of the university. He said Governor Wike also suspended the on-going employment exercise at the university, adding that a committee has been set up to investigate the exercise and report back in two weeks.  JUST IN: Governor Wike sacks Rivers University Vice Chancellor Cultists kill final year student of Rivers University Ahmed appoints Ag. VC for KWASU Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin